ygData.subject: Re: Missed Notes
ygData.msgSnippet: ... It s hard to have sympathy for you, when you turn a suggested explanation into an irrelevant attack on my brass skills.  If you ve done testing, then show
ygData.messageBody:
"Chris Kuenster (Entex)" wrote:

> From: "Chris Kuenster (Entex)" <v-ntxck@...>
>
> As I said, my skills are all at or above 190, and approaching 200. My
> regrets that your Brass skills are poor, perhaps a little practice is in
> order. I have tested this and as I said several times I am missing notes on
> songs I NEVER missed notes on before.

It's hard to have sympathy for you, when you turn a suggested explanation into
an irrelevant attack on my brass skills. If you've done testing, then show us
the numbers. So far everyone who has posted numbers, as far as I can tell, is
showing perfectly reasonable missed note rates. If you have evidence to the
contrary, if anyone does, we can start to reasonably believe there's a
difference, but most people seem to not be experiencing what you are.

I don't think it is server specific, btw, since John Kim, who also says his
missed note rates are up, is on the same server as I am, and I haven't
experienced it.

Jyzan
